CONTEXT LongObjectId IN ENGLISH
{- Regression test for OBJECT atom-identity shortening.

   LongObjectId.xlsx populates `label` with one Thing whose identity is 300 characters long.
   Thing has TType OBJECT, so the compiler must shorten that identity to 254 characters
   (<first 243 chars>_<10 hex chars of sha1(id)>, see shortenObjectId / Atom::setId). Without
   shortening the 300-char id would not fit the VARCHAR(255) column and `ampersand validate`
   would fail when it populates MariaDB. The rules below force the populated (shortened) Thing
   identity through the generated SQL, so validate also checks Haskell-vs-SQL agreement on it. -}

REPRESENT Thing TYPE OBJECT
REPRESENT Name TYPE ALPHANUMERIC

RELATION label[Thing*Name] [UNI]
INCLUDE "LongObjectId.xlsx"

RULE labelTotalOnPopulated : I[Thing] |- label;label~
MEANING "Every Thing that occurs in the population has a label."

ENDCONTEXT
